Hello?

01:06.055 --> 01:07.379
This is ADT. Is
everything all right?

01:07.389 --> 01:09.129
No.
- Is someone in the house?

01:09.139 --> 01:11.212
No. I-I don't know.
I'm here by myself.

01:11.222 --> 01:13.337
Please, just have somebody come.
Please come.

01:13.347 --> 01:14.379
I'll just stay on the line,
okay?

01:14.389 --> 01:15.837
Yes, ma'am.

01:15.847 --> 01:17.753
All clear. No sign of entry.

01:17.763 --> 01:19.379
And you checked everything?

01:19.389 --> 01:20.629
Yes, we checked all over.

01:20.639 --> 01:21.920
In the morning,

01:21.930 --> 01:23.753
you might want to check
with your alarm company.

01:23.763 --> 01:25.337
I looked at your alarm system,

01:25.347 --> 01:27.546
and it looks like the kitchen
window area has malfunctioned.

01:27.556 --> 01:31.462
Okay. Thank you. Good night.

01:37.014 --> 01:44.920
♪ ♪

01:44.930 --> 01:47.379
Hey, can I come over?

01:47.389 --> 01:50.170
No--uh, my alarm went off.

01:50.180 --> 01:54.045
I'm--no, I'm fine.
It's just, I'm--I'm scared.

01:56.055 --> 01:57.879
Look, if it's a problem, I can
just go to my parents' house.

01:57.889 --> 01:59.837
I just thought
that you might want to--

02:03.222 --> 02:05.045
Okay.

02:05.055 --> 02:06.296
Thank you.

02:06.306 --> 02:14.306
♪ ♪

02:35.055 --> 02:36.504
You want something to drink?

02:36.514 --> 02:39.795
Yeah.
Whatever you're having, please.

02:41.598 --> 02:44.879
Um, what were you reading
before I came over?

02:44.889 --> 02:49.920
Oh, I recently won
in an auction some slave papers

02:49.930 --> 02:52.129
that I was enjoying.

02:52.139 --> 02:54.629
Or not enjoying.

02:54.639 --> 02:56.087
Do you mind?

02:58.763 --> 03:00.045
Sure.

03:01.805 --> 03:03.379
These are the actual letters?

03:03.389 --> 03:08.296
Yes, I've been collecting
love letters between slaves

03:08.306 --> 03:10.504
for quite some time now.

03:10.514 --> 03:13.546
You should exhibit these.

03:13.556 --> 03:20.504
Well, I've been talking
to the Reginald F. Lewis Museum

03:20.514 --> 03:23.546
for African American History
& Culture

03:23.556 --> 03:26.504
about doing
a permanent installation.

03:26.514 --> 03:28.795
Or the Smithsonian.
I mean, these are amazing.

03:28.805 --> 03:29.962
Yeah.

03:29.972 --> 03:31.462
Wow.

03:35.180 --> 03:37.337
You've been
through a lot tonight.

03:37.347 --> 03:39.254
Let's get you some rest.

03:44.639 --> 03:46.753
Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

03:55.763 --> 04:00.212
Oh, um, would you mind
sleeping on that side?

04:00.222 --> 04:02.087
Uh, oh. Yeah, no.

04:02.097 --> 04:03.254
No problem.

04:03.264 --> 04:04.920
You gonna join me?

04:04.930 --> 04:09.795
Uh, I'm going to finish
reading those letters.

04:09.805 --> 04:11.337
Uh, I don't want
to rub it in,

04:11.347 --> 04:14.129
but I don't have
to work tomorrow.

04:14.139 --> 04:16.170
So you should get some rest.

04:16.180 --> 04:17.588
Great.

04:17.598 --> 04:18.629
All right.

04:21.639 --> 04:25.588
