05:42.472 --> 05:50.421
♪ And I seem to find
the happiness I seek ♪

05:50.431 --> 05:55.879
♪ When we're out together,
dancing cheek to cheek ♪

05:55.889 --> 05:57.296
You're still in bed?

05:59.639 --> 06:01.004
Did you ever sleep?

06:01.014 --> 06:02.753
I nap.

06:04.139 --> 06:05.795
You hungry?

06:05.805 --> 06:08.920
Yeah.

06:08.930 --> 06:10.753
Sure.

06:12.514 --> 06:14.879
Hey, did you ever call
your alarm company?

06:14.889 --> 06:16.421
No.

06:16.431 --> 06:17.588
You should get on that.

06:17.598 --> 06:18.753
You know,
you're a celebrity now.

06:18.763 --> 06:21.170
You've been
thrust into the spotlight

06:21.180 --> 06:23.379
with that ugly black woman
story.

06:23.389 --> 06:25.962
Yeah. No, I'm on it. Thanks.

06:25.972 --> 06:29.212
Are you?

06:29.222 --> 06:34.129
Well, not right this second,
'cause it's 7:30 in the morning.

06:34.139 --> 06:35.753
Are you okay?

06:35.763 --> 06:37.421
I'm fine.
I'm just worried about you.

06:41.180 --> 06:43.212
Are we in a relationship?

06:46.763 --> 06:48.753
I've been operating
as though we are.

06:48.763 --> 06:51.337
Really?
- Yeah.

06:51.347 --> 06:54.254
When were you gonna tell me?

06:54.264 --> 06:56.296
I didn't think
I needed to say it.

06:56.306 --> 06:59.004
Oh, well, a girl loves
to hear these things.

07:03.014 --> 07:07.753
You know, your omelet
tastes better when it's hot.

07:07.763 --> 07:09.753
Does it?
- Mm-hmm.

07:09.763 --> 07:13.004
Unless you'd like
to skip it altogether.

07:13.014 --> 07:15.129
I would love to.

07:15.139 --> 07:18.087
But remember
some of us have to work, so...

07:18.097 --> 07:20.504
I respect that.

07:20.514 --> 07:21.753
Enjoy.

07:24.180 --> 07:27.962
Hey, did you
move my toothbrush?

07:27.972 --> 07:29.962
What?

07:29.972 --> 07:32.962
Where's my toothbrush?

07:32.972 --> 07:35.753
Oh, just get another one
from the cabinet.

07:39.014 --> 07:40.753
Your phone's ringing.

07:50.930 --> 07:51.962
Hey, Val. What's up?

07:51.972 --> 07:53.170
Sorry to call so late.

07:53.180 --> 07:54.337
No, it's okay.

07:54.347 --> 07:55.753
Where do we go
for late-night noodles?

07:55.763 --> 07:58.296
Oh, we went to, um,
Octopus Bar

07:58.306 --> 07:59.920
in East Atlanta on Gresham.

07:59.930 --> 08:01.254
Oh, Gresham. Yeah, that's it.

08:01.264 --> 08:02.462
Yeah, no problem.

08:02.472 --> 08:04.004
Has David called?
- Huh?

08:04.014 --> 08:05.753
I just thought
you might have heard from him.

08:05.763 --> 08:07.462
No, I haven't. Why?

08:07.472 --> 08:09.254
Monk died.

08:09.264 --> 08:12.920
He'd been sick for a while, so
David decided to put him down.

08:14.055 --> 08:17.296
Yeah, um, I'm here.

08:17.306 --> 08:18.588
He was old, you know.

08:18.598 --> 08:19.795
His vet only saw it
getting worse,

08:19.805 --> 08:23.546
so David finally made
the decision.

08:23.556 --> 08:25.504
Wow. Okay, um--
- I'm sorry.

08:25.514 --> 08:27.504
No, I appreciate you
telling me. I--

08:27.514 --> 08:30.004
I know you loved
that dog too.

08:30.014 --> 08:33.004
Have you or Chris
seen him since?

08:33.014 --> 08:35.379
I haven't yet, but Chris
has been checking in on him.

08:35.389 --> 08:36.462
Oh, okay--okay.

08:36.472 --> 08:38.087
That's--that's good.

08:38.097 --> 08:39.794
I'm sorry to be the one
to tell you.

08:39.804 --> 08:43.212
Yeah, I-I-I'll just
talk to you later, okay, Val?

08:43.222 --> 08:44.920
Okay, honey. Bye.

08:44.930 --> 08:46.462
All right.

08:49.763 --> 08:51.254
Everything okay?

08:51.264 --> 08:53.629
Yeah.

08:53.639 --> 08:55.546
You seem upset.

08:58.763 --> 09:03.753
I just found out my ex
had to put his dog to sleep,

09:03.763 --> 09:06.588
and I'm pretty sure he's...
devastated.

09:06.598 --> 09:09.212
Mm.

09:09.222 --> 09:11.296
You should call him,

09:11.306 --> 09:13.546
make sure he's all right.

09:13.556 --> 09:17.212
Why would you encourage me
to call my ex?

09:17.222 --> 09:18.379
Why wouldn't I?

09:18.389 --> 09:21.337
I mean,
it'd make you feel better

09:21.347 --> 09:22.920
to know that he's okay,

09:22.930 --> 09:26.546
and I'm sure it'd benefit him
to know that you care.

09:29.306 --> 09:31.337
See, that's the casualty
of breaking up.

09:31.347 --> 09:35.045
You don't get to call your ex
about their dead dog.

10:15.139 --> 10:17.004
Hey.
- Hey.

10:17.014 --> 10:19.212
I'm angry, and unfortunately
this is the only place

10:19.222 --> 10:20.753
I feel safe enough
to express it.

10:20.763 --> 10:23.629
May I?
- Sure.

10:24.847 --> 10:26.504
They want me to leave,

10:26.514 --> 10:28.337
but they won't let me leave
with my dignity.

10:28.347 --> 10:29.962
I have done everything I can

10:29.972 --> 10:33.296
except call lawyers in
for the long fight.

10:33.306 --> 10:35.045
I think you can help.

10:35.055 --> 10:36.421
Oh, Cynthia, I don't want
to get involved in the middle

10:36.431 --> 10:37.795
of your negotiations, please.

10:37.805 --> 10:40.337
At least let me beg
before you turn me away.

10:42.097 --> 10:44.087
Look, I--
you don't deserve this.

10:44.097 --> 10:46.546
I'm just at my wit's end,
and I need to get out of here.

10:46.556 --> 10:48.212
No. Please.

10:48.222 --> 10:49.629
I will listen.

10:51.763 --> 10:53.087
Please.

10:57.222 --> 11:00.379
Just make sure you get
a live sign-off in your deal.

11:00.389 --> 11:01.837
They're trying
to screw me out of mine.

11:01.847 --> 11:03.254
What?
- Yep.

11:03.264 --> 11:04.588
They want me to do
a taped sign-off,

11:04.598 --> 11:06.170
afraid I might say something
live.

11:06.180 --> 11:08.753
I mean, this is just
such a psycho business.

11:08.763 --> 11:11.045
Oh, you can't smoke in here.
- Oh, the hell I can't.

11:11.055 --> 11:12.421
You know, just when
things get bad, they get--

11:12.431 --> 11:13.753
it's like they get worse.

11:13.763 --> 11:15.879
No, Cynthia,
don't light up in my office.

11:18.930 --> 11:20.296
Look, I'm sorry that you're
going through this.

11:20.306 --> 11:21.337
I really am.

11:21.347 --> 11:23.753
Wow.

11:23.763 --> 11:26.879
Save your sorries
for yourself, Mary Jane.

11:26.889 --> 11:29.504
You have no idea
what you've agreed to.

11:32.139 --> 11:34.546
<i>I used to watch this show, Fame.</i>

11:34.556 --> 11:37.296
Too old for you, but there was
this feisty little black woman.

11:37.306 --> 11:38.629
Debbie Allen.
- Yeah. I guess.

11:38.639 --> 11:42.170
And she used to say,
"You want fame?

11:42.180 --> 11:45.129
Well, fame costs."

11:45.139 --> 11:47.753
Never truer words
were said in this business.

11:47.763 --> 11:49.296
You'll see.

11:49.306 --> 11:51.129
I'm honestly shocked.

11:51.139 --> 11:52.629
I-I just thought
it was standard.

11:52.639 --> 11:55.087
Yeah, well,

11:55.097 --> 11:57.753
you only get what you
negotiate for in this life.

12:00.180 --> 12:02.087
If you're not gonna help me,
say you're not gonna help me.

12:02.097 --> 12:03.753
If you're not gonna do it,
say you're not gonna--

12:03.763 --> 12:06.045
Be quiet. I
want to say something.

12:06.055 --> 12:08.045
Everybody.

12:08.055 --> 12:10.337
Be quie--I want to say
something.

12:11.347 --> 12:14.962
Paul. Shut them up.

12:14.972 --> 12:16.379
Everybody, listen, listen.

12:16.389 --> 12:18.588
Quiet down. Quiet down, please.

12:18.598 --> 12:20.254
Steven, I want
you to go back on the money.

12:20.264 --> 12:21.920
Quiet.

12:21.930 --> 12:23.087
And I want you
to ask for a sign-off.

12:23.097 --> 12:24.546
Come on, quiet down.
- Why not?

12:24.556 --> 12:25.629
Thank you, baby.

12:25.639 --> 12:28.004
Now, I know there are folks

12:28.014 --> 12:30.421
who didn't believe
we would see this day,

12:30.431 --> 12:31.753
but I knew,

12:31.763 --> 12:33.753
just like I knew
I could give birth to him

12:33.763 --> 12:35.879
when everybody was saying
it was impossible.

12:35.889 --> 12:40.837
Well, that's what my baby does:
the impossible.

12:40.847 --> 12:45.753
Five years undergrad,
one year at law school,

12:45.763 --> 12:49.379
and three years at architectural
school at Georgia Tech.

12:49.389 --> 12:51.920
Whoo, whoo!
- Big-time.

12:51.930 --> 12:55.629
And he didn't
take any extra time.

12:55.639 --> 12:58.337
See, there you go.
- My goodness.

12:58.347 --> 12:59.962
We're so proud of you, baby.

12:59.972 --> 13:02.379
You did it. You didn't quit.

13:02.389 --> 13:05.920
Some people didn't believe it,
but a mother knows.

13:05.930 --> 13:07.753
Yeah, and now everyone knows.

13:07.763 --> 13:09.753
Grandma's been on the phone
all day

13:09.763 --> 13:13.129
talking about job offers
in "Los An-ge-les."

13:14.972 --> 13:18.421
There it is. L.A., baby.
- Wow.

13:18.431 --> 13:20.753
And why not?

13:20.763 --> 13:23.753
After all,
this is a time to celebrate.

13:23.763 --> 13:27.962
To my P.J. Congratulations.

13:27.972 --> 13:29.588
All: Congratulations.

13:29.598 --> 13:31.129
Thank you.

13:31.139 --> 13:33.629
Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

13:33.639 --> 13:34.753
Cheers.

13:36.556 --> 13:39.045
And thank you, Mom and Dad,

13:39.055 --> 13:43.004
for believing in me,
for supporting me.

13:43.014 --> 13:45.753
All right, I'm truly blessed.
Seriously.

13:45.763 --> 13:48.129
Oh, and I don't have any student
loans to pay off, so boom.

13:48.139 --> 13:53.753
None. I'm debt-free, baby.

13:53.763 --> 13:57.588
But, um, in all seriousness,
um, thank you,

13:57.598 --> 14:01.170
because you both promised
you'd give us an education,

14:01.180 --> 14:03.753
the tools of true freedom.

14:03.763 --> 14:07.296
And my journey's really just
beginning.

14:07.306 --> 14:08.421
I hope I make you proud.

14:08.431 --> 14:09.588
I hope you move out soon.

14:09.598 --> 14:11.546
Oh, yes.
- Stay in the kitchen.

14:11.556 --> 14:13.753
I second that.
- Whatever.

14:13.763 --> 14:15.004
No, no. My little brother.

14:15.014 --> 14:17.212
He just graduated.
No, no, it's okay.

14:17.222 --> 14:18.254
We got to get this done.

14:18.264 --> 14:19.504
Seriously, thank you,
Mom, Dad.

14:19.514 --> 14:21.962
Since we are all here,

14:21.972 --> 14:24.504
we may as well share
our good news.

14:24.514 --> 14:25.546
Yes.

14:25.556 --> 14:27.170
Me, Kenny, and the girls

14:27.180 --> 14:29.546
are moving to North Carolina.

14:29.556 --> 14:33.962
Me and my... fiancé have
both found jobs there.

14:33.972 --> 14:35.504
Whoa. Wait, what?

14:35.514 --> 14:38.753
It's "fiancé and I," Ni.

14:38.763 --> 14:41.045
Ma, she--
- Your what?

14:42.472 --> 14:44.087
You're--you're getting married?

14:44.097 --> 14:46.045
Wait, Naomi,
you're getting married?

14:46.055 --> 14:47.920
Kenny, where's the ring?

14:47.930 --> 14:49.795
I mean, she can't get married
without a ring.

14:49.805 --> 14:51.087
Uh-uh. I don't want one.
I want a house.

14:51.097 --> 14:52.795
Wait, Naomi,
you're getting married

14:52.805 --> 14:54.129
and you're moving where?

14:54.139 --> 14:55.546
Uh, North Carolina.

14:55.556 --> 14:57.629
I'm working at the pharmacy
at the new Kroger there.

14:57.639 --> 15:00.087
Hey. Congratulations.
- Thank you.

15:00.097 --> 15:03.296
Wow. Okay.

15:03.306 --> 15:05.129
Okay, well, congratulations.

15:05.139 --> 15:07.004
Um, I think--

15:07.014 --> 15:09.462
I guess that's two reasons
to celebrate this--this, uh--

15:09.472 --> 15:12.753
Absolutely.
- Aw!

15:12.763 --> 15:13.837
He's losing his baby girl.

15:13.847 --> 15:15.504
Aww, Boukie!

15:15.514 --> 15:16.795
Aw.

15:16.805 --> 15:19.170
Papi.

15:19.180 --> 15:22.920
So what you think, Niecy?

15:22.930 --> 15:24.879
You haven't said anything.

15:24.889 --> 15:30.045
Um, that's because I'm
so excited for you guys.

15:30.055 --> 15:31.629
Congratulations.

15:31.639 --> 15:33.753
Yeah. That's great.

15:33.763 --> 15:35.129
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

15:35.139 --> 15:38.045
Well, it's all fine
for you and Kitty, you know,

15:38.055 --> 15:42.421
but today,
we're celebrating Paul Jr.

15:42.431 --> 15:43.462
Yeah, thank you. Yeah.

15:43.472 --> 15:45.753
All right, Stu.

15:46.847 --> 15:48.546
Bye.

15:48.556 --> 15:49.629
Cake time.

15:49.639 --> 15:52.753
Sorry you had to pick up
the cake.

15:52.763 --> 15:53.879
I told my mom I would do it.

15:53.889 --> 15:54.889
I don't mind.

15:58.139 --> 15:59.588
Congratulations.

15:59.598 --> 16:01.462
I heard you're getting
the prime-time spot.

16:01.472 --> 16:03.753
Hopefully. Still negotiating.

16:03.763 --> 16:05.629
Yeah.

16:09.055 --> 16:10.462
You hear about
David's dog dying?

16:12.598 --> 16:13.753
Very sad.

16:22.347 --> 16:24.212
Cake, anyone?

16:24.222 --> 16:26.087
Ladies eat first.

16:35.689 --> 16:39.120
Hey.
- Hi.

16:39.130 --> 16:40.412
How did you get in?

16:40.422 --> 16:42.621
Oh, the door was unlocked.

16:42.631 --> 16:46.329
Oh. How did you get
past the gate?

16:46.339 --> 16:47.496
Is there a problem?

16:47.506 --> 16:50.662
No. Well, yes,
if my gate is broken.

16:50.672 --> 16:52.953
No, I just punched in the code.

16:53.672 --> 16:54.788
Who gave you the code?

16:54.798 --> 16:56.120
I just watched your driver
do it.

16:56.130 --> 16:57.579
It was four 1s.

16:57.589 --> 16:59.454
Really easy and very unsafe.

16:59.464 --> 17:01.412
I learned a lot of dos
and don'ts

17:01.422 --> 17:04.079
when I was talking
to the alarm company.

17:04.089 --> 17:06.329
Oh, Jesus, I got to take this.

